# Go-FFI Coding Conventions

## Type Aliases and Usage
- Use the provided `Any` type alias instead of `interface{}`
- Use the provided `Dict` type alias instead of `map[string]Any` when dealing with PureScript records
- Use `[]Any` for arrays

## Parameter Naming Conventions
1. For parameters used as-is (no type assertion needed):
   - Use the parameter name without a trailing underscore
   ```go
   exports["foo"] = func(bar Any) Any {
       return bar
   }
   ```

2. For parameters requiring type assertion:
   - Name the input parameter with a trailing underscore
   - Create a type-inferred variable without the underscore
   ```go
   exports["foo"] = func(bar_ Any) Any {
       bar := bar_.(int)
       // ... rest of the code
   }
   ```

 3. To apply curried PureScript functions from within Go code use Apply it works for any arity
   ```go
    result := Apply(fn, arg1, arg2)
   ```

 4. To run functions that return Effect use Run
   ```go
    result := Run(someEffect)
   ```

## PureScript to Go Type Mappings

| PureScript Type | Go Type                    |
|----------------|-----------------------------|
| Array          | []Any                       |
| String         | string                      |
| Number         | float64                     |
| Int            | int                         |
| Char           | string (single UTF-8 entity)|
| Boolean        | bool                        |
| Records        | map[string]Any              | 